# spec-resistance — Nature submission GitHub repo
# Selective upload: keep only reproducibility-essential content.
# Internal pipeline scratch, raw logs, draft IRB materials, and giant CSVs
# are excluded. The CSVs live in the standalone backup repo
# (https://github.com/FelipeMAffonso/spec-resistance-extended-backup).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Internal pipeline / scratch (not for public reproducibility)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
add_new_models/
prereg/
logs/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. IRB — keep only the approval letter, drop everything else
# (prep guide, recruitment templates, eligibility screener are internal)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IRB/IRB_PREP_GUIDE.md
IRB/eligibility_screening.docx
IRB/eligibility_screening.md
IRB/recruitment_prolific.docx
IRB/recruitment_prolific.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Harness — drop debugging/recovery script
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
harness/fix_broken_judges.py

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3b. Study 3 per-session conversation traces — too granular for the repo
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
human_studies/study3-chatbot/kv_export.json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3c. Editor-facing submission materials — these belong in the Nature
# portal upload, not in the public reproducibility repo. The repo's job
# is to let a third party reproduce the manuscript; the cover letter,
# response to editor, and reviewer suggestions are private to the
# author/editor exchange.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
paper/cover_letter.md
paper/cover_letter.pdf
paper/response_to_editor.md
paper/editor-correspondence.md
paper/suggested_reviewers.md
paper/reporting_summary_draft.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Large CSVs — too big for the main repo, hosted in backup repo
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/spec_resistance_CLEAN.csv
data/spec_resistance_EXTENDED.csv
data/spec_resistance_NEW_MODELS.csv
data/spec_resistance_CLEAN.csv.gz
data/extended_csv_backup/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. Build artifacts and caches
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
*.egg-info/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Compiled paper artifacts that should be regenerated, not tracked
# (manuscript .pdf and .docx ARE included for reviewer convenience —
#  exception below ensures `paper/main.pdf` etc. are tracked)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
paper/_templates/__pycache__/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. Local environment / secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.venv/
venv/
*.key
*.pem
config/.env
config/.env.local

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. OS / editor noise
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
